1
00:00:02,102 --> 00:00:04,536
<i>[ Phone Beeping ]</i>

2
00:00:06,673 --> 00:00:08,540
[ Ringing ]
[ Miss Parker ]
WHAT?

3
00:00:08,609 --> 00:00:10,475
[ Jarod ]
ALWAYS THE WORKAHOLIC.
JAROD--

4
00:00:10,544 --> 00:00:14,146
TORMENTING HOURS
ARE FROM 9:00 TO 5:00.
CALL BACK TOMORROW.

5
00:00:14,214 --> 00:00:16,215
WHO SAID I WAS CALLING
TO TORMENT YOU?

6
00:00:16,283 --> 00:00:18,717
MAYBE I WAS JUST
FEELING NOSTALGIC.

7
00:00:18,786 --> 00:00:22,187
IF YOU'RE FEELING HOMESICK,
COME VISIT.

8
00:00:22,255 --> 00:00:24,189
I HAVE A ROOM ALL READY FOR YOU.

9
00:00:24,257 --> 00:00:27,526
GENEROUS OFFER,
BUT I WILL REGRETFULLY DECLINE.

10
00:00:27,595 --> 00:00:29,794
SO. WHAT IS IT, JAROD?

11
00:00:29,863 --> 00:00:33,164
I WAS HOPING YOU'D GIVE MY BEST
TO THE REST OF OUR
DYSFUNCTIONAL FAMILY.

12
00:00:33,233 --> 00:00:35,467
PARTICULARLY MR. RAINES.

13
00:00:35,536 --> 00:00:38,837
OH, I'LL BE SURE
TO SAY HEY,
NEXT TIME I SEE HIM.

14
00:00:38,906 --> 00:00:41,573
WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
YOU SAW HIM?

15
00:00:41,642 --> 00:00:43,575
<i>HE HASN'T BEEN AROUND</i>
<i>MUCH LATELY, HAS HE?</i>

16
00:00:43,644 --> 00:00:46,545
I COUNT RAINES'S ABSENCE
AS A BLESSING.
I DON'T QUESTION IT.

17
00:00:46,613 --> 00:00:48,680
<i>IF YOU DON'T QUESTION,</i>

18
00:00:48,749 --> 00:00:51,049
YOU DON'T LEARN.
[ Beeps ]

19
00:00:53,420 --> 00:00:57,022
I BROUGHT THE
TRIUMVIRATE PHONE LOGS
YOU REQUESTED.

20
00:00:57,090 --> 00:01:01,592
BACK BURNER, BROOTS.
I HAVE A HOLIER CRUSADE
FOR YOU.

21
00:01:01,661 --> 00:01:03,995
FIND OUT WHERE RAINES
HAS BEEN LATELY.

22
00:01:05,065 --> 00:01:06,998
<i> [ Ringing ]</i>

23
00:01:09,436 --> 00:01:11,670
<i> [ Ringing Continues ]</i>

24
00:01:11,738 --> 00:01:14,506
[ Beeps ]
HELLO?

25
00:01:14,575 --> 00:01:17,075
<i> WELL, IT'S</i>
<i> ABOUT DAMN TIME.</i>
<i> TELL ME YOU FOUND HIM.</i>

26
00:01:17,144 --> 00:01:19,077
<i> LOOK, I'M PAYING YOU</i>
<i> ALL THIS MONEY...</i>

27
00:01:19,146 --> 00:01:21,079
<i> 'CAUSE YOU'RE SUPPOSED</i>
<i> TO BE ON THE INSIDE.</i>

28
00:01:21,148 --> 00:01:23,014
THIS BOY SHOULD
BE DEAD BY NOW.

29
00:01:25,752 --> 00:01:27,686
<i> BOLTON, MINNESOTA</i>
<i> MUST BE A PODUNK,</i>
<i> NOTHING TOWN.</i>

30
00:01:27,754 --> 00:01:30,155
HOW HARD CAN IT BE
TO FIND HIM?

31
00:01:30,223 --> 00:01:33,292
WELL, HE GOES
TO SCHOOL, DOESN'T HE?

32
00:01:33,360 --> 00:01:35,294
THE CLOCK IS TICKING.

33
00:01:35,362 --> 00:01:37,562
MY NEW TRIAL IS IN FIVE DAYS,

34
00:01:37,631 --> 00:01:41,533
AND THIS BOY'S TESTIMONY
IS THE ONLY THING
THAT THEY'VE GOT ON ME.

35
00:01:41,602 --> 00:01:44,269
<i> I WANT YOU TO FIND HIM.</i>

36
00:01:44,338 --> 00:01:46,771
I WANT YOU TO KILL HIM.
OTHERWISE, YOU'RE DEAD.

37
00:01:46,840 --> 00:01:49,207
<i> GOT ME?</i>
<i> DON'T LET ME DOWN.</i>

38
00:01:56,216 --> 00:01:58,583
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM, BUDDY?
YOU IN SOME KIND
OF HURRY?

39
00:01:58,652 --> 00:02:00,752
YEAH.

40
00:02:00,820 --> 00:02:03,054
AS A MATTER OF FACT, I AM.

41
00:02:05,125 --> 00:02:07,058
<i>[ Bell Ringing ]</i>

42
00:02:08,963 --> 00:02:11,730
[ Chattering ]

43
00:02:15,569 --> 00:02:17,502
[ Claps ]
GOOD MORNING, CLASS.

44
00:02:17,571 --> 00:02:19,504
MY NAME IS MR. BRODIE.

45
00:02:19,573 --> 00:02:21,506
I'M YOUR SUBSTITUTE TEACHER.

46
00:02:22,742 --> 00:02:25,877
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>
<i>THERE ARE PRETENDERS AMONG US.</i>

47
00:02:25,945 --> 00:02:27,879
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>I WAS TAKEN FROM MY FAMILY.</i>

48
00:02:27,948 --> 00:02:31,516
<i>THIRTY-SIX HOURS AND HE'S</i>
<i>ALREADY DEMONSTRATING MORE</i>
<i>TALENT THAN ANY OF OUR OTHERS.</i>

49
00:02:31,585 --> 00:02:34,987
<i>HOW MANY PEOPLE DIED</i>
<i>BECAUSE OF WHAT I THOUGHT UP?</i>

50
00:02:35,055 --> 00:02:38,489
SINCE I BROKE OUT,
I'VE SPENT EVERY MOMENT
SEARCHING FOR MY PAST.

51
00:02:38,558 --> 00:02:40,758
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>HE'S A PRETENDER--</i>

52
00:02:40,827 --> 00:02:43,595
<i>A GENIUS WHO CAN BECOME</i>
<i>ANYONE THAT HE WANTS TO BE.</i>

53
00:02:43,663 --> 00:02:46,398
-<i> THE CENTRE WANTS HIM ALIVE.</i>
- PREFERABLY.

54
00:02:46,466 --> 00:02:49,401
<i>- [ Miss Parker ] HE DEFENDS</i>
<i>  THE WEAK AND ABUSED.</i>
<i>- [ Jarod ] LIFE'S A GIFT.</i>

55
00:03:01,181 --> 00:03:03,648
-<i> YOU A DOCTOR?</i>
- I AM TODAY.

56
00:03:42,322 --> 00:03:45,090
MR. CONKLIN,
YOUR REGULAR TEACHER,

57
00:03:45,158 --> 00:03:47,425
IS ON VACATION,
SO BEFORE WE GET STARTED,

58
00:03:47,494 --> 00:03:50,194
I'D LIKE TO GET TO KNOW
ALL OF YOU A LITTLE BIT BETTER.

59
00:03:50,263 --> 00:03:52,497
DO YOU KNOW ABOUT SEX?
[ Laughter ]

60
00:03:57,771 --> 00:04:00,172
<i> MR. CONKLIN SAID WE'RE</i>
<i> GONNA START OUR SEX</i>
<i> EDUCATION THIS WEEK.</i>

61
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:03,074
MY MOM SIGNED
A PERMISSION SLIP.
<i>KEVIN--</i>

62
00:04:03,143 --> 00:04:05,843
INTERESTED IN BIOLOGY.
GOOD.

63
00:04:05,912 --> 00:04:08,680
<i>[ Boy ]</i>
<i>I ALREADY KNOW ABOUT SEX.</i>

64
00:04:08,748 --> 00:04:12,016
- MY DAD HAS THE INTERNET.
- JOEL-- LIKES COMPUTERS.

65
00:04:13,420 --> 00:04:16,454
<i> MR. BRODIE?</i>
<i> ARE YOU MARRIED?</i>

66
00:04:16,523 --> 00:04:18,590
UH, NO, UH, GEMMA.

67
00:04:18,659 --> 00:04:21,292
- I'M NOT.
- DO YOU HAVE A GIRLFRIEND?

68
00:04:21,361 --> 00:04:24,562
-<i> YEAH. DOES SHE KNOW</i>
<i> ABOUT SEX?</i>
- [ Laughter ]

69
00:04:24,631 --> 00:04:27,866
I'M THE ONE THAT'S
SUPPOSED TO BE ASKING
THE QUESTIONS, REMEMBER?

70
00:04:27,934 --> 00:04:31,603
WHAT ABOUT YOU, UH, MATTHEW?

71
00:04:31,672 --> 00:04:34,406
-<i> WHAT ARE YOU</i>
<i> INTERESTED IN?</i>
- UH--

72
00:04:34,475 --> 00:04:36,408
I LIKE TO READ, I GUESS.

73
00:04:36,477 --> 00:04:38,877
YOU LIKE TO READ.
THAT'S A GOOD THING.

74
00:04:39,947 --> 00:04:42,046
AND YOU, UH, ERIC.

75
00:04:42,115 --> 00:04:44,715
<i> WHAT ARE YOUR INTERESTS?</i>

76
00:04:44,784 --> 00:04:48,319
COOL STUFF. ESPIONAGE.
COUNTERINTELLIGENCE.

77
00:04:48,388 --> 00:04:51,289
YOU KNOW, I COULD TELL YOU MORE,
BUT, UH, I'D HAVE TO KILL YOU.

78
00:04:51,357 --> 00:04:53,959
<i>[ Laughter ]</i>

79
00:04:54,028 --> 00:04:55,793
ERIC'S A FREAK!
HE CAN'T EVEN WRITE.

80
00:04:55,862 --> 00:04:58,129
IT'S ALL GIBBERISH.
IT'S NOT GIBBERISH, JOEL.

81
00:04:58,198 --> 00:05:00,331
<i>IT'S A SECRET CODE,</i>
<i>SO KNUCKLE-DRAGGING MOPES...</i>

82
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:02,333
LIKE YOU CAN'T READ IT.
OH, YEAH?

83
00:05:02,402 --> 00:05:05,937
IT'S PROBABLY A LOVE LETTER
TO YOUR GIRLFRIEND MOLLY
OVER THERE.

84
00:05:06,006 --> 00:05:09,006
<i> [ Laughter ]</i>

85
00:05:09,075 --> 00:05:12,510
ALL RIGHT. CAN WE, UH,
GET BACK ON TRACK HERE?

86
00:05:12,579 --> 00:05:16,915
- [ Laughing, Chattering ]
- UH, CLASS.

87
00:05:16,983 --> 00:05:19,684
- CLASS.
- [ Laughing, Chattering
Continue ]

88
00:05:19,753 --> 00:05:22,954
<i> ENOUGH!</i>
<i> [ Whistles ]</i>

89
00:05:23,023 --> 00:05:25,623
<i> COULD YOU CUT ME</i>
<i> A LITTLE SLACK HERE?</i>

90
00:05:25,692 --> 00:05:28,526
IT'S NOT EASY BEING
THE NEW KID IN SCHOOL.

91
00:05:28,595 --> 00:05:31,929
I'LL BET SOME OF YOU
KNOW ABOUT THAT.

92
00:05:31,998 --> 00:05:35,200
<i> TELL ME SOMETHING.</i>
<i> HOW MANY OF YOU</i>
<i> WERE BORN HERE?</i>

93
00:05:35,269 --> 00:05:38,269
HOW MANY OF YOU SPENT
YOUR WHOLE LIFE IN BOLTON?

94
00:05:42,743 --> 00:05:46,211
<i>MR. BRODIE? I WAS BORN HERE,</i>
<i>BUT MY BROTHER WASN'T.</i>

95
00:05:46,280 --> 00:05:48,546
OKAY. AND HOW MANY OF YOU
HAVE BROTHERS AND SISTERS?

96
00:05:52,085 --> 00:05:56,087
-<i> DOES THIS MEAN WE'RE NOT</i>
<i> GONNA LEARN ABOUT SEX?</i>
-<i> [ Laughter ]</i>

97
00:05:56,155 --> 00:05:59,123
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>IT WAS A CHILD'S</i>
<i>EYEWITNESS TESTIMONY...</i>

98
00:05:59,192 --> 00:06:02,527
THAT SEALED ESPOSITO'S FATE
TO A LIFE IN PRISON.

99
00:06:02,596 --> 00:06:07,164
HOWEVER, JUST LAST MONTH
THE COURT GRANTED ESPOSITO
A NEW TRIAL...

100
00:06:07,233 --> 00:06:09,300
BASED ON A PROCEDURAL
TECHNICALITY.

101
00:06:09,369 --> 00:06:11,803
THE CHARGES AGAINST ESPOSITO
STEM FROM THE BRUTAL MURDER...

102
00:06:11,872 --> 00:06:13,805
OF A BROOKLYN SHOP OWNER.

103
00:06:13,874 --> 00:06:18,109
ACCORDING TO POLICE,
ESPOSITO BLUDGEONED AND THEN
BURIED THE VICTIM'S BODY,

104
00:06:18,177 --> 00:06:20,778
UNAWARE THE CRIME WAS BEING
WITNESSED BY A FIFTH GRADER...

105
00:06:20,847 --> 00:06:24,482
ON A FIELD TRIP FROM NEARBY
WOODBURY ELEMENTARY SCHOOL.

106
00:06:39,599 --> 00:06:41,900
<i>WHAT'S OUR RULE</i>
<i>ABOUT OTHER PEOPLE'S THINGS?</i>

107
00:06:41,969 --> 00:06:46,404
- EXCUSE ME.
- THOSE AREN'T YOUR FILES,
ARE THEY?

108
00:06:46,473 --> 00:06:50,174
UH, NO, BUT THERE WAS
NOBODY IN THE OFFICE
SO I JUST--

109
00:06:50,243 --> 00:06:54,746
OUR RULE ABOUT
OTHER PEOPLE'S THINGS
IS, "WE DON'T TOUCH THEM."

110
00:06:54,815 --> 00:06:58,249
- I UNDERSTAND, BUT THERE WAS--
- BUTTS BELONG IN ASHTRAYS,
MISTER.

111
00:06:58,318 --> 00:07:01,986
<i>IT'S ALL RIGHT, MRS. WARNER.</i>
<i>JAROD'S OUR NEW</i>
<i>SIXTH GRADE TEACHER.</i>

112
00:07:02,055 --> 00:07:05,757
I'LL EXPECT THOSE BACK,
YOUNG MAN.

113
00:07:05,826 --> 00:07:08,293
<i> DON'T WORRY</i>
<i> ABOUT MRS. WARNER.</i>
<i> SHE'S A LIFER.</i>

114
00:07:08,362 --> 00:07:10,561
- A LIFER?
- BEEN HERE 32 YEARS.

115
00:07:10,630 --> 00:07:13,898
TEACHING A 10-YEAR-OLD
IS THE ONLY LANGUAGE SHE KNOWS.

116
00:07:13,967 --> 00:07:17,101
KIND OF SCARY, ISN'T IT?
JUST LIKE BEING IN GRADE
SCHOOL ALL OVER AGAIN.

117
00:07:17,170 --> 00:07:19,771
OR FOR THE VERY FIRST TIME. HI.

118
00:07:19,839 --> 00:07:23,041
HI.
JAROD, RACHEL DALY,
OUR STUDENT COUNSELOR.

119
00:07:23,110 --> 00:07:25,043
JAROD'S TAKING OVER
THE SIXTH GRADERS
WHILE MR. CONKLIN'S IN HAWAII.

120
00:07:25,112 --> 00:07:28,613
YOU BELIEVE CONKLIN'S LUCK?
HE'S ALWAYS BEEN TALKING
ABOUT HAWAII,

121
00:07:28,682 --> 00:07:30,515
AND OUT OF NOWHERE
HE WINS A TRIP.

122
00:07:30,584 --> 00:07:32,450
SAID HE DIDN'T EVEN
REMEMBER ENTERING THE CONTEST.

123
00:07:32,519 --> 00:07:34,719
HMM. UNBELIEVABLE.
WELL, IF YOU'LL
EXCUSE ME,

124
00:07:34,788 --> 00:07:37,889
I'VE GOT A FOURTH GRADER
WHO IS HABITUALLY
PULLING FIRE ALARMS.

125
00:07:37,957 --> 00:07:40,157
NICE TO MEET YOU,
JAROD.
NICE TO MEET YOU.

126
00:07:40,226 --> 00:07:43,328
PRINCIPAL BAUER,
WHILE I'VE GOT YOU HERE--

127
00:07:43,396 --> 00:07:46,864
I HAVE A STUDENT IN MY CLASS--
UH, MATTHEW REESE.

128
00:07:46,933 --> 00:07:49,834
<i>HIS RECORDS ONLY</i>
<i>GO BACK 11 MONTHS,</i>
<i>AND BEFORE THAT...</i>

129
00:07:49,903 --> 00:07:53,104
- IT'S LIKE HE DOESN'T EXIST.
- MATTHEW ONLY MOVED HERE
LAST YEAR.

130
00:07:53,173 --> 00:07:56,107
BUT EVEN STILL,
WOULDN'T HIS OLD SCHOOL
TRANSFER THE RECORDS OVER?

131
00:07:56,176 --> 00:07:59,176
<i> NORMALLY, BUT ACCORDING</i>
<i> TO HIS MOM, HIS LAST</i>
<i> SCHOOL HAD A FIRE.</i>

132
00:07:59,245 --> 00:08:01,479
<i> ALL THE FILES</i>
<i> WERE DESTROYED.</i>

133
00:08:01,547 --> 00:08:04,115
WELL.

134
00:08:04,184 --> 00:08:06,618
I GUESS THAT EXPLAINS IT.

135
00:08:14,494 --> 00:08:17,328
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>RAINES HAS BEEN GOING</i>
<i>TO AN INSANE ASYLUM?</i>

136
00:08:17,397 --> 00:08:20,665
UH, THE PRATT INSTITUTE.
IT'S ABOUT AN HOUR
SOUTH OF HERE.

137
00:08:20,734 --> 00:08:23,167
HE'S BEEN GOING
A COUPLE OF TIMES A DAY.

138
00:08:23,236 --> 00:08:26,103
LOOK. THERE HE IS.

139
00:08:26,172 --> 00:08:28,840
CUE MEN WITH
BIG BUTTERFLY NETS.
NO, NO. HE'S NOT A PATIENT.

140
00:08:28,909 --> 00:08:30,975
HE'S VISITING SOMEONE.
THERE'S A WOMAN.

141
00:08:32,178 --> 00:08:34,345
<i> A WOMAN WHO MEANS</i>
<i> SOMETHING TO JAROD.</i>

142
00:08:34,414 --> 00:08:37,549
<i> THE QUESTION IS,</i>
<i> WHO IS SHE?</i>
<i>[ Sydney ] MY GOD.</i>

143
00:08:39,552 --> 00:08:41,485
SYDNEY?

144
00:08:42,923 --> 00:08:45,523
-<i> [ Sydney ] IT'S EDNA RAINES.</i>
- RAINES'S WIFE?

145
00:08:45,592 --> 00:08:48,626
- IT'S IMPOSSIBLE.
- KICK THE ROCK OVER, SYD.
WHAT AM I NOT SEEING?

146
00:08:48,695 --> 00:08:51,696
EDNA RAINES COMMITTED SUICIDE
MORE THAN 20 YEARS AGO.

147
00:08:51,765 --> 00:08:54,365
OR SO
YOU WERE TOLD.

148
00:08:54,434 --> 00:08:56,868
<i> BROOTS, GET A TOWN CAR.</i>
<i>NO, IT'S TOO LATE.</i>

149
00:08:56,937 --> 00:08:58,903
THE GUY AT THE HOSPITAL
TOLD ME SHE ESCAPED LAST NIGHT.

150
00:09:04,644 --> 00:09:08,579
<i>[ Children Laughing,</i>
<i>  Chattering ]</i>

151
00:09:13,987 --> 00:09:16,354
<i> OKAY, A TEACHER'S PAY</i>
<i> IS ONE THING, JAROD,</i>

152
00:09:16,423 --> 00:09:19,157
[ Laughing ]
BUT EATING
THE SCHOOL LUNCH--

153
00:09:19,226 --> 00:09:22,160
WHAT, DO YOU HAVE
A DEATH WISH?
I WAS INTRIGUED.

154
00:09:22,229 --> 00:09:26,030
A TUBE OF PROCESSED MEAT
COVERED BY A DEEP-FRIED
CARBOHYDRATE...

155
00:09:26,099 --> 00:09:28,266
AND SKEWERED WITH A STICK
SO THAT IT'S FULLY PORTABLE.

156
00:09:28,335 --> 00:09:32,870
- SORT OF A MEAT POPSICLE.
- IS THAT YOUR FIRST CORN DOG?

157
00:09:36,243 --> 00:09:38,676
MMM. GOOD.
<i> [ Laughs ]</i>

158
00:09:38,745 --> 00:09:40,845
YOU'RE MUCH BRAVER
THAN I AM.

159
00:09:43,082 --> 00:09:45,082
<i>I'VE NOTICED THAT MATTHEW</i>
<i>DOESN'T SOCIALIZE MUCH...</i>

160
00:09:45,151 --> 00:09:47,084
WITH THE OTHER CHILDREN.

161
00:09:47,153 --> 00:09:49,253
ARE THERE ANY ISSUES
ABOUT HIM I SHOULD KNOW ABOUT?

162
00:09:49,322 --> 00:09:52,624
MATTHEW'S BEEN A LITTLE
SLOW ASSIMILATING SINCE
HE TRANSFERRED HERE,

163
00:09:52,692 --> 00:09:55,760
<i> BUT SOME KIDS</i>
<i> ARE JUST LIKE THAT.</i>

164
00:09:55,828 --> 00:09:58,863
- WHY THE INTEREST?
- I JUST FIGURE THE MORE
I KNOW ABOUT MY KIDS,

165
00:09:58,932 --> 00:10:01,198
THE MORE I CAN HELP THEM.

166
00:10:08,341 --> 00:10:11,175
<i>[ Esposito ]</i>
<i>THREE DAYS AND COUNTING.</i>

167
00:10:11,244 --> 00:10:13,544
I DON'T WANT TO HEAR
YOU'RE GETTING CLOSE.

168
00:10:13,613 --> 00:10:16,047
I WANT TO HEAR
THAT THIS KID IS DEAD.

169
00:10:16,116 --> 00:10:18,716
IF YOU CAN'T FIGURE OUT
WHICH BOY IT IS
AND GET THIS JOB DONE,

170
00:10:18,785 --> 00:10:22,553
THEN I'M GONNA
COME DO IT MYSELF.

171
00:10:22,622 --> 00:10:25,890
YOU BETTER WORRY
THAT I JUST DON'T
BURY YOU WITH HIM.

172
00:10:34,301 --> 00:10:36,301
<i> [ Doorbell Rings ]</i>

173
00:10:43,476 --> 00:10:45,743
- HELLO.
- HI.

174
00:10:45,812 --> 00:10:48,413
MY SON SAID THAT THERE
WAS A NEW TEACHER
IN TOWN,

175
00:10:48,482 --> 00:10:51,015
SO I WANTED TO BRING YOU
A LITTLE SOMETHING
TO SAY WELCOME.

176
00:10:51,084 --> 00:10:53,083
THAT'S VERY NICE.
THANK YOU.
OH!

177
00:10:53,152 --> 00:10:56,287
IT'S HOT.
I'D PROBABLY BETTER DO THIS.

178
00:10:56,356 --> 00:10:58,589
I KNOW WHAT IT'S LIKE
TO BE NEW IN TOWN.

179
00:10:58,658 --> 00:11:01,459
MATTHEW AND I JUST
MOVED HERE OURSELVES
LAST YEAR.

180
00:11:01,528 --> 00:11:04,028
YOU SAID, UH, MATTHEW.
MATTHEW REESE?

181
00:11:04,097 --> 00:11:07,465
OH! I'M HIS MOM.
I DIDN'T SAY THAT,
DID I?

182
00:11:07,534 --> 00:11:09,601
- NO.
- NO.
[ Laughs ]

183
00:11:09,669 --> 00:11:12,370
WHERE DID YOU TWO
MOVE HERE FROM?

184
00:11:12,439 --> 00:11:14,372
FROM BACK EAST.

185
00:11:14,441 --> 00:11:17,108
<i> [ Doorbell Rings ]</i>

186
00:11:18,878 --> 00:11:20,979
EXCUSE ME.

187
00:11:24,383 --> 00:11:28,052
- HELLO.
- UH, HELLO.

188
00:11:29,856 --> 00:11:32,657
- HELLO, JUSTINE.
- HELLO, GAIL.

189
00:11:32,726 --> 00:11:34,659
YOU TWO
KNOW EACH OTHER?
YEAH.

190
00:11:34,728 --> 00:11:38,162
WE'RE IN THE SAME
SINGLE MOMS' COOKING GROUP
HERE IN TOWN.

191
00:11:38,231 --> 00:11:40,298
OH, UH--
MMM.

192
00:11:40,367 --> 00:11:42,400
<i> [ Doorbell Rings ]</i>

193
00:11:57,317 --> 00:12:00,151
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>IT'S PRETTY COOL, HUH?</i>

194
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:03,487
YOU CAN SEE A WHOLE WORLD
OF THINGS THAT ARE TOO SMALL
TO SEE WITH YOUR HUMAN EYE.

195
00:12:03,556 --> 00:12:06,190
HEY, MAYBE WE
CAN USE IT TO SEE
ERIC'S TINY LITTLE BRAIN.

196
00:12:06,259 --> 00:12:09,526
- [ Laughter ]
- MR. BRODIE, HOW DO THEY
SWIM AROUND LIKE THAT?

197
00:12:09,595 --> 00:12:11,662
THAT'S A VERY GOOD QUESTION.

198
00:12:11,731 --> 00:12:14,098
WHY DON'T YOU ALL
READ CHAPTER FOUR
AND FIND OUT?

199
00:12:14,167 --> 00:12:16,201
[ Students Groaning ]
I LOST THAT BOOK.

200
00:12:16,269 --> 00:12:18,236
[ Chuckles ]
GET TO WORK.

201
00:12:22,342 --> 00:12:24,408
- IT'S PRETTY NEAT, HUH?
- YEAH.

202
00:12:24,477 --> 00:12:26,710
BUT I'VE SEEN PROTOZOANS
AND STUFF BEFORE.

203
00:12:26,779 --> 00:12:29,680
WE HAD MICROSCOPES
IN THE SCIENCE ROOM
AT MY OLD SCHOOL.

204
00:12:29,749 --> 00:12:33,083
DID YOU LIKE YOUR OLD SCHOOL?
I GUESS.

205
00:12:33,153 --> 00:12:35,086
MUST HAVE BEEN PRETTY TOUGH--

206
00:12:35,155 --> 00:12:37,388
LEAVING YOUR OLD FRIENDS
LIKE THAT.

207
00:12:37,457 --> 00:12:40,258
MOM SAID WE DIDN'T
HAVE A CHOICE.
WE HAD TO MOVE.

208
00:12:42,195 --> 00:12:45,897
I'M NOT REALLY SUPPOSED
TO TALK ABOUT IT.
<i>[ Bell Ringing ]</i>

209
00:13:05,018 --> 00:13:07,218
COME ON, JOEL.
THAT'S FOR MY EYES ONLY.

210
00:13:07,286 --> 00:13:09,554
OH.

211
00:13:09,622 --> 00:13:12,256
I'M SORRY, DUDE.
HERE.

212
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:16,294
[ Laughs ]

213
00:13:16,362 --> 00:13:19,129
THIS IS SWEET.
IT'S WAY OVER YOUR HEAD.

214
00:13:19,198 --> 00:13:20,998
OH, YEAH? LET'S FIND OUT.

215
00:13:24,370 --> 00:13:29,473
HI. I'M ERIC GANTRY,
AND I'M A SCRAWNY LITTLE FREAK,

216
00:13:29,542 --> 00:13:31,775
AND I'M SO MADLY IN LOVE
WITH MOLLY.

217
00:13:34,047 --> 00:13:39,483
<i>[ Joel On Recorder ]</i>
<i>HI. I'M ERIC GANTRY,</i>
<i>AND I'M A SCRAWNY LITTLE FREAK,</i>

218
00:13:39,552 --> 00:13:42,119
<i>AND I'M SO MADLY IN LOVE</i>
<i>WITH MOLLY.</i>

219
00:13:42,188 --> 00:13:44,589
WHAT'S OUR RULE
ABOUT OTHER PEOPLE'S
THINGS, JOEL?

220
00:13:44,657 --> 00:13:48,459
WHAT?
WE DO NOT TOUCH THEM.

221
00:13:52,098 --> 00:13:54,031
PRETTY MANLY, FREAK--

222
00:13:54,100 --> 00:13:57,368
<i>ALWAYS HAVING A TEACHER</i>
<i>RESCUE YOU.</i>

223
00:14:16,389 --> 00:14:18,889
IT SEEMS
HE HAS IT IN FOR YOU.

224
00:14:18,958 --> 00:14:22,126
IT'S NO BIG DEAL.

225
00:14:22,194 --> 00:14:24,629
WHAT'S A SECRET
AGENT WITHOUT
AN ARCHENEMY, RIGHT?

226
00:14:26,432 --> 00:14:29,466
JUST FORGET ABOUT IT.

227
00:14:37,543 --> 00:14:40,477
-<i> HEY!</i>
-<i> [ Car Starts ]</i>

228
00:14:42,415 --> 00:14:45,016
[ Tires Screeching ]
HEY!

229
00:14:49,256 --> 00:14:51,722
[ Sydney ]
I STILL CAN'T
BELIEVE EDNA'S ALIVE.

230
00:14:51,791 --> 00:14:53,891
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>YOU SOUND AS IF</i>
<i>YOU LIKED HER, SYD.</i>

231
00:14:57,464 --> 00:14:59,897
THERE WAS SOMETHING
MORE ALIVE ABOUT HER.

232
00:14:59,966 --> 00:15:03,200
THERE'S ALSO SOMETHING
FAMILIAR ABOUT HER.

233
00:15:03,269 --> 00:15:05,703
SHE WAS WORKING
AS A PHYSICIAN,
RIGHT HERE AT THE CENTRE,

234
00:15:05,772 --> 00:15:08,939
IN THE STAFF DISPENSARY.
RIGHT.

235
00:15:09,008 --> 00:15:11,108
IN FACT, I THINK SHE SAW ME
WHEN I HAD THE MUMPS.

236
00:15:11,177 --> 00:15:15,079
-<i> YOUR MOTHER TRUSTED HER</i>
<i>  COMPLETELY.</i>
- SHE DID?

237
00:15:15,147 --> 00:15:18,583
EDNA, YOU SEE, HAD
MANY ADMIRABLE QUALITIES.

238
00:15:18,652 --> 00:15:21,185
SHE WAS AS VOCAL
IN COMMUNITY POLITICS...

239
00:15:21,254 --> 00:15:24,021
AS SHE WAS AT CENTRE
COCKTAIL PARTIES.

240
00:15:24,090 --> 00:15:27,525
HOW DID SHE END UP
MARRYING RAINES?

241
00:15:27,594 --> 00:15:30,395
AFTER THE MURDER
OF THEIR DAUGHTER,
EDNA FELL APART.

242
00:15:30,464 --> 00:15:33,031
I WAS TOLD SHE TOOK
AN OVERDOSE OF BARBITURATES.

243
00:15:34,501 --> 00:15:37,568
I WAS AT THE FUNERAL, PARKER.

244
00:15:37,636 --> 00:15:40,371
I WONDER WHAT'S
REALLY BURIED OUT THERE
IN THE CENTRE CEMETERY.

245
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:42,573
I'VE GOT BROOTS OUT
HUNTING FOR EDNA.

246
00:15:42,641 --> 00:15:44,608
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>
<i>RAINES MUST BE DOING THE SAME.</i>

247
00:15:44,678 --> 00:15:47,645
<i> I THINK IT'S TESTING</i>
<i> HIS NEW-FOUND INNER PEACE.</i>

248
00:15:47,714 --> 00:15:51,915
<i> [ Knocking ]</i>
NOT A WORD TO ANYONE, SYDNEY.
GOOD NIGHT.

249
00:15:54,053 --> 00:15:57,555
BROOTS, TELL ME SOMETHING GOOD.

250
00:15:58,992 --> 00:16:03,293
<i>OH, IT'S SO GOOD</i>
<i>TO SEE YOU AGAIN, CATHERINE.</i>

251
00:16:09,903 --> 00:16:12,002
<i>[ Bell Ringing ]</i>
GREAT LITTLE TOWN
LIKE BOLTON--

252
00:16:12,071 --> 00:16:14,505
NEVER THOUGHT WE'D HAVE
SICKOS HANGING AROUND
OUR SCHOOL.

253
00:16:14,574 --> 00:16:16,507
DID YOU GET
A GOOD LOOK AT HIM?

254
00:16:16,576 --> 00:16:20,578
NO, AND HE DIDN'T STICK
AROUND FOR QUESTIONS.
REMINDS ME.

255
00:16:20,647 --> 00:16:24,148
KIDS ARE HAVING
A BIG DANCE ON FRIDAY--
SADIE HAWKINS--

256
00:16:24,216 --> 00:16:28,452
<i>IN LIGHT OF YESTERDAY,</i>
<i>I'D FEEL BETTER IF WE HAD</i>
<i>ANOTHER CHAPERONE THERE.</i>

257
00:16:28,521 --> 00:16:32,156
OH. I LOOK FORWARD TO IT.
AND I CAN'T WAIT
TO MEET THIS MISS HAWKINS.

258
00:16:36,929 --> 00:16:40,130
WAIT, HONEY.
FORGOT YOUR LUNCH.

259
00:16:40,199 --> 00:16:42,934
REMEMBER,
I'M WORKING LATE, OKAY?
SO LEFTOVERS FOR DINNER.

260
00:16:43,002 --> 00:16:45,669
<i> BYE.</i>
EXCUSE ME, MRS. GANTRY.

261
00:16:45,738 --> 00:16:48,205
<i>MY NAME IS JAROD BRODIE.</i>
<i>I'M ERIC'S NEW TEACHER.</i>

262
00:16:48,275 --> 00:16:51,042
I WAS WONDERING
IF I COULD TALK TO YOU
ABOUT SOME TROUBLE HE'S HAVING.

263
00:16:51,111 --> 00:16:54,979
OH, YOU MEAN JOEL?
YEAH, ERIC TOLD ME
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED YESTERDAY.

264
00:16:55,048 --> 00:16:56,948
JOEL IS A BIT OF A PROBLEM.

265
00:16:57,016 --> 00:17:00,484
BUT YOU THINK
ERIC'S ALL RIGHT OTHERWISE?

266
00:17:00,553 --> 00:17:03,954
- "OTHERWISE"?
- OH, YOU KNOW,
I JUST WORRY, THAT'S ALL.

267
00:17:04,023 --> 00:17:06,557
YOU KNOW, WITH THIS WHOLE
"SECRET AGENT"...

268
00:17:06,626 --> 00:17:08,960
SPY GAME OF HIS.

269
00:17:09,029 --> 00:17:10,961
PRETENDING ISN'T SO BAD.

270
00:17:11,030 --> 00:17:14,031
YEAH, AS LONG AS
HE'S NOT HIDING IN IT.

271
00:17:14,100 --> 00:17:18,002
BUT IT IS THE SIXTH GRADE.
I'M PROBABLY JUST
BEING SILLY.

272
00:17:18,070 --> 00:17:20,838
HEY, IT'S NOT SILLY
TO CARE ABOUT YOUR SON.

273
00:17:20,907 --> 00:17:22,840
I'LL HAVE A TALK WITH HIM.

274
00:17:22,909 --> 00:17:25,476
<i>[ Bell Ringing ]</i>
THANK YOU.

275
00:17:27,547 --> 00:17:30,814
<i>EXCUSE ME, MRS. WARNER.</i>
<i>THE PARKING STICKER</i>
<i>YOU GAVE ME--</i>

276
00:17:30,883 --> 00:17:33,017
I CAN'T FIND IT ANYWHERE.
I MUST HAVE LOST IT.

277
00:17:34,386 --> 00:17:37,588
BOYS-- THEY'D LOSE THEIR HEADS
IF THEY WEREN'T ATTACHED.

278
00:17:37,657 --> 00:17:40,224
WELL, TECHNICALLY,
LACK OF CRANIAL ATTACHMENT...

279
00:17:40,293 --> 00:17:43,761
WOULD NULLIFY
ALL OTHER MOTOR SKILLS,
THEREFORE THE NOTION--

280
00:17:43,830 --> 00:17:47,565
UH, IF IT HELPS, I BELIEVE
IT WAS STICKER NUMBER 48.

281
00:17:51,271 --> 00:17:54,438
NO, MR. BRODIE, YOU HAD 55.

282
00:17:54,507 --> 00:17:57,808
NUMBER 48 BELONGS
TO LARRY GRASSO,
OUR JANITOR.

283
00:17:58,811 --> 00:18:00,744
THANK YOU.

284
00:18:07,654 --> 00:18:09,620
MR. BRODIE! HI.

285
00:18:10,623 --> 00:18:12,757
<i>MATTHEW FORGOT HIS LUNCH.</i>

286
00:18:12,826 --> 00:18:15,092
SO, I HAVE JUST BEEN
DYING TO KNOW...

287
00:18:15,161 --> 00:18:17,161
WHAT YOU THOUGHT
OF MY RISOTTO.

288
00:18:17,230 --> 00:18:20,298
ACTUALLY, I WAS--
I WAS GOING TO CALL YOU.

289
00:18:20,366 --> 00:18:22,099
REALLY?

290
00:18:22,168 --> 00:18:24,302
THE OTHER EVENING,
WHEN I WAS ASKING YOU
THE QUESTIONS...

291
00:18:24,370 --> 00:18:27,271
ABOUT WHERE
YOU USED TO LIVE--

292
00:18:27,340 --> 00:18:29,440
I KNOW WHY
YOU WERE DODGING THEM.

293
00:18:29,509 --> 00:18:31,141
DID-- DID I GIVE YOU
THAT IMPRESSION?

294
00:18:31,210 --> 00:18:34,979
GAIL, I KNOW WHY
YOU AND MATTHEW
HAD TO MOVE HERE.

295
00:18:35,048 --> 00:18:37,014
YOU CAN TRUST ME.

296
00:18:37,083 --> 00:18:39,016
REALLY.

297
00:18:41,254 --> 00:18:43,354
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
HOW HARD IT'S BEEN,

298
00:18:43,423 --> 00:18:45,723
KEEPING THIS A SECRET
AND LIVING THIS LIE.

299
00:18:45,792 --> 00:18:48,159
I MEAN, I-I THOUGHT
THAT HE WAS A NICE GUY.

300
00:18:48,228 --> 00:18:51,095
YOU KNOW, I HAD NO IDEA
ABOUT THE HIDDEN CAMERA.

301
00:18:51,164 --> 00:18:53,330
I GUESS EVERYONE'S
GOT THE INTERNET THESE DAYS.

302
00:18:53,399 --> 00:18:56,701
- AND-- AND BEFORE YOU KNEW IT--
- YOU NEVER LIVED IN WOODBURY?

303
00:18:56,769 --> 00:19:00,537
THERE WAS NO TESTIMONY,
NO TRIAL?

304
00:19:00,606 --> 00:19:02,439
TRIAL?

305
00:19:06,045 --> 00:19:08,011
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>
<i>HOW IS EDNA?</i>

306
00:19:08,081 --> 00:19:11,482
<i> AS VACANT</i>
<i> AS THE BATES MOTEL.</i>

307
00:19:13,352 --> 00:19:16,186
EDNA? DO YOU REMEMBER ME?

308
00:19:16,255 --> 00:19:19,323
WE WERE COLLEAGUES
AT THE CENTRE,

309
00:19:19,391 --> 00:19:22,459
- MANY, MANY YEARS AGO.
- SYDNEY.

310
00:19:22,528 --> 00:19:24,595
<i>THAT'S RIGHT.</i>

311
00:19:24,664 --> 00:19:26,964
YOU<i> DO</i> REMEMBER.

312
00:19:28,501 --> 00:19:31,936
EDNA? EDNA, CAN YOU HEAR ME?

313
00:19:32,005 --> 00:19:35,205
FORGET IT, SYD.
SHE'S BEEN CLAP-ON,
CLAP-OFF ALL AFTERNOON.

314
00:19:35,274 --> 00:19:38,876
TWENTY YEARS OF SEDATION
MUST HAVE TAKEN A DAMAGING
TOLL ON HER BRAIN.

315
00:19:38,945 --> 00:19:40,912
BUT SOMETHING
BROUGHT HER HERE--

316
00:19:40,980 --> 00:19:43,181
SOMETHING BROUGHT HER HERE
LOOKING FOR MY MOTHER.

317
00:19:43,249 --> 00:19:45,850
- WHAT?
- LET'S TRY AND FIND OUT.

318
00:19:45,919 --> 00:19:49,019
WELL, THERE'S ONLY
ONE REASON THE CENTRE
WOULD HAVE GONE TO...

319
00:19:49,088 --> 00:19:51,388
SUCH LENGTHS TO KEEP HER QUIET.

320
00:19:51,457 --> 00:19:53,957
<i> SHE KNOWS THEIR</i>
<i> DIRTY LITTLE SECRETS.</i>

321
00:19:54,026 --> 00:19:55,959
I WANT TO KNOW THEM TOO.

322
00:19:56,028 --> 00:19:58,662
EVEN IF EDNA WERE LUCID,

323
00:19:58,731 --> 00:20:01,532
<i>SHE MAY NOT HAVE</i>
<i>THE CAPACITY TO TELL YOU.</i>

324
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:03,867
WELL, THIS DIG ISN'T OVER.

325
00:20:03,936 --> 00:20:05,969
TAKES ONE TO KNOW ONE, RIGHT?

326
00:20:06,038 --> 00:20:08,706
MAYBE WE SHOULD
PASS THE SHOVEL TO ANGELO,

327
00:20:08,774 --> 00:20:11,942
<i> AND SEE WHAT HE</i>
<i> CAN FIND IN THERE.</i>

328
00:20:27,360 --> 00:20:29,660
<i>[ Eric ]</i>
<i>TOUGH DAY, HUH?</i>

329
00:20:29,729 --> 00:20:34,065
I'M AFRAID SO, ERIC.
DID YOU JUST GET
SOME BAD NEWS?

330
00:20:34,134 --> 00:20:36,367
YEAH.

331
00:20:36,435 --> 00:20:38,369
WOW.

332
00:20:38,438 --> 00:20:42,206
THAT'S SOME
PRETTY SOPHISTICATED
SPY EQUIPMENT YOU GOT THERE.

333
00:20:42,274 --> 00:20:44,207
WHAT'S THAT THING?

334
00:20:44,276 --> 00:20:47,578
HEY, LOOK AT THIS--
AN OPERATIVE'S COMMUNICATOR.

335
00:20:47,646 --> 00:20:50,914
- YOU KNOW, SO MY SUPERIORS
CAN CONTACT ME.
- WHEN YOU'RE ON A MISSION.

336
00:20:50,983 --> 00:20:53,751
ERIC, JOEL WAS KIND
OF A JERK YESTERDAY,

337
00:20:53,819 --> 00:20:57,555
THE WAY HE WAS MAKING FUN OF YOU
IN FRONT OF EVERYBODY
LIKE THAT.

338
00:20:57,623 --> 00:20:59,557
I TRY NOT TO LET HIM
GET TO ME.

339
00:20:59,626 --> 00:21:03,093
I DON'T REALLY CARE
WHAT HE OR ANY OF THE OTHER
NON-OPERATIVES THINK.

340
00:21:03,162 --> 00:21:06,863
EXCEPT FOR MOLLY, RIGHT?
I SEE THE WAY
YOU LOOK AT HER.

341
00:21:06,932 --> 00:21:08,866
THAT'S SUPPOSED TO BE
TOP SECRET.

342
00:21:08,935 --> 00:21:12,135
AGAIN, STUPID JOEL
COMPROMISED EVERYTHING.

343
00:21:12,204 --> 00:21:14,271
CHECK THIS OUT.

344
00:21:16,709 --> 00:21:18,642
I KEEP ALL MY SECRETS
IN HERE.

345
00:21:18,711 --> 00:21:21,712
YOU DON'T EXACTLY HAVE
THE PROPER CLEARANCE,

346
00:21:21,781 --> 00:21:24,114
BUT, UH, I'LL MAKE
AN EXCEPTION.

347
00:21:24,183 --> 00:21:26,950
WHOA.

348
00:21:27,019 --> 00:21:30,454
- A SURVEILLANCE PHOTO.
NICE GOING.
- SHE PROBABLY HATES ME.

349
00:21:30,523 --> 00:21:33,457
NAH. NO, YOU GOT THAT
DASHING SPY-THING GOING ON.

350
00:21:33,526 --> 00:21:35,459
GIRLS LOVE THAT.

351
00:21:35,528 --> 00:21:39,262
STILL, WHAT DO I DO?
WELL, IF I WERE YOU,
I WOULD JUST...

352
00:21:39,331 --> 00:21:41,965
FACE IT HEAD ON
AND TELL HER HOW YOU FEEL.

353
00:21:42,034 --> 00:21:45,002
NO WAY. SUICIDE MISSION.

354
00:21:45,071 --> 00:21:48,105
WHEN YOU CARE ABOUT SOMEBODY,
YOU'VE GOTTA TELL THEM...

355
00:21:48,173 --> 00:21:50,273
WHILE YOU'VE GOT THE CHANCE.

356
00:21:50,342 --> 00:21:52,443
I WOULDN'T KNOW
WHAT TO SAY.

357
00:21:54,646 --> 00:21:56,613
HERE.

358
00:21:56,683 --> 00:21:59,684
PRACTICE INTO THIS THING,
AND WHEN YOU GET IT RIGHT,

359
00:21:59,752 --> 00:22:01,752
TELL HER.

360
00:22:01,821 --> 00:22:04,021
<i>[ Bell Ringing ]</i>

361
00:22:05,591 --> 00:22:07,758
MR. BRODIE?

362
00:22:07,827 --> 00:22:10,761
THANKS.

363
00:22:10,830 --> 00:22:13,130
YOU'RE THE FIRST FRIEND
I'VE MADE SINCE I CAME HERE.

364
00:22:20,105 --> 00:22:22,873
<i>[ Eric's Voice ]</i>
<i>YOU'RE THE FIRST FRIEND I MADE</i>
<i>SINCE I CAME HERE.</i>

365
00:22:22,942 --> 00:22:25,976
<i>[ Jarod's Voice ]</i>
<i>HOW MANY OF YOU SPENT</i>
<i>YOUR WHOLE LIFE IN BOLTON?</i>

366
00:22:27,613 --> 00:22:29,546
<i>[ Eric ]</i>
<i>I KEEP ALL MY SECRETS IN HERE.</i>

367
00:23:04,416 --> 00:23:06,817
<i>[ Thinking ]</i>
<i>WOODBURY.</i>

368
00:23:10,089 --> 00:23:12,356
<i>ERIC IS THE WITNESS.</i>

369
00:23:22,068 --> 00:23:24,201
MRS. WARNER,
HAVE YOU SEEN ERIC GANTRY?

370
00:23:24,270 --> 00:23:27,504
HE WAS TALKING TO THE JANITOR
A FEW MINUTES AGO.
THEN I SAW HIM WALKING HOME.

371
00:23:27,573 --> 00:23:30,440
DAMN IT.
MR. BRODIE!

372
00:23:50,629 --> 00:23:53,197
THIS IS AGENT X-4
CHECKING IN.

373
00:24:09,815 --> 00:24:12,216
<i>ERIC! ERIC!</i>

374
00:24:12,284 --> 00:24:14,251
[ Tires Screeching ]

375
00:24:22,494 --> 00:24:24,427
ERIC! ERIC!

376
00:24:27,467 --> 00:24:29,900
<i>WHAT HAPPENED?</i>
<i>WHERE'S ERIC?</i>

377
00:24:29,968 --> 00:24:32,836
I WAS TRYING
TO HELP THE KID.

378
00:24:34,874 --> 00:24:38,909
YOU'RE A U.S. MARSHAL.
<i> THERE'S A LEAK INSIDE</i>
<i> WITNESS PROTECTION.</i>

379
00:24:38,978 --> 00:24:41,212
I WAS JUST ABOUT
TO PULL ERIC IN.

380
00:24:41,280 --> 00:24:44,248
THEY'RE GONNA KILL HIM
IF YOU DON'T STOP THEM.
WHO?

381
00:24:44,316 --> 00:24:46,983
- WHO SHOT YOU?
- DIDN'T SEE HIM.

382
00:24:47,052 --> 00:24:49,553
<i> GOTTA BE ESPOSITO'S</i>
<i> INSIDE MAN.</i>

383
00:24:49,622 --> 00:24:52,155
YOU HANG ON.
I'M GOING TO GET SOME HELP.

384
00:24:52,224 --> 00:24:54,992
<i> SAVE ERIC.</i>
<i> THE KILLER KNOWS</i>
<i> WHERE HE LIVES.</i>

385
00:24:55,061 --> 00:24:57,027
<i> DON'T LET HIM</i>
<i> GO HOME, JAROD.</i>

386
00:24:57,096 --> 00:24:59,497
DON'T LET HIM GO HOME.

387
00:25:03,836 --> 00:25:07,104
OPERATIVE'S COMMUNICATOR.
SO MY SUPERIORS
CAN CONTACT ME.

388
00:25:11,210 --> 00:25:13,177
[ Beeping ]

389
00:25:35,367 --> 00:25:37,668
[ Beeping ]

390
00:26:01,160 --> 00:26:03,994
[ Muffled Cries ]
SHH, SHH. IT'S ME.
COME ON.

391
00:26:04,063 --> 00:26:06,897
BACK TO MY HOUSE.
LET'S GET YOUR MOM.

392
00:26:06,966 --> 00:26:10,667
WHEN I HEARD THAT ANIMAL
GOT OUT, I WAS, UH--
I WAS SO SCARED.

393
00:26:10,736 --> 00:26:13,503
BUT THEN
WITNESS PROTECTION CALLED
AND THEY SAID NOT TO WORRY,

394
00:26:13,572 --> 00:26:15,972
THAT THEY WERE
SENDING SOMEONE OUT
TO KEEP AN EYE ON US.

395
00:26:16,041 --> 00:26:20,911
THE JANITOR.
ESPOSITO'S MAN
ALREADY GOT TO HIM.

396
00:26:20,980 --> 00:26:22,746
MY GOD.

397
00:26:22,815 --> 00:26:25,515
THEY GAVE ME A NUMBER TO CALL
IN CASE OF AN EMERGENCY.

398
00:26:25,584 --> 00:26:28,518
YOU CAN'T.
THERE'S A LEAK
INSIDE THE AGENCY.

399
00:26:28,587 --> 00:26:30,587
IT'S NOT SAFE.

400
00:26:30,656 --> 00:26:33,490
OKAY. OKAY,
SO WHAT DO WE DO?
WE CALL THE POLICE?

401
00:26:33,559 --> 00:26:35,926
MY GUT SAYS THAT WE STAY
UNDER EVERYBODY'S RADAR--

402
00:26:35,995 --> 00:26:37,928
AT LEAST FOR TONIGHT.

403
00:26:37,997 --> 00:26:39,930
SIT DOWN AND TRY TO RELAX.

404
00:26:42,167 --> 00:26:45,336
MR. BRODIE,
I AM SO, SO SORRY...

405
00:26:45,404 --> 00:26:48,104
THAT I LIED IN CLASS
WHEN YOU ASKED WHO'S
LIVED HERE A LONG TIME.

406
00:26:48,173 --> 00:26:51,207
<i> I MEAN, THEY TOLD ME</i>
<i> THAT SOMETIMES I HAD</i>
<i> TO LIE.</i>

407
00:26:51,276 --> 00:26:53,477
IT'S NOT LIKE I WANTED TO.
<i>ERIC--</i>

408
00:26:53,545 --> 00:26:55,512
YOU DID THE RIGHT THING.

409
00:27:08,094 --> 00:27:10,060
MOM, I'M DONE.
<i> OKAY, HONEY.</i>

410
00:27:10,129 --> 00:27:13,863
<i> HEY. THERE'S EIGHT</i>
<i> CARTONS OF ICE CREAM</i>
<i> IN THE FREEZER.</i>

411
00:27:13,932 --> 00:27:16,867
AFTER YOUR HOMEWORK.

412
00:27:22,074 --> 00:27:24,675
- HE'S A TERRIFIC KID.
- YEAH.

413
00:27:24,743 --> 00:27:27,645
YOU TWO HAVE BEEN
THROUGH A LOT.

414
00:27:27,713 --> 00:27:31,982
YEAH, BUT HE'S JUST A BOY,
AND HE DESERVES A CHILDHOOD...

415
00:27:32,051 --> 00:27:34,017
<i>SURROUNDED BY FAMILY</i>
<i>AND FRIENDS,</i>

416
00:27:34,086 --> 00:27:36,520
<i>AND INSTEAD HE WAS HUSTLED AWAY</i>
<i>IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT,</i>

417
00:27:36,589 --> 00:27:38,555
TAKEN AWAY FROM EVERYTHING.

418
00:27:38,624 --> 00:27:40,891
IT'S NOT FAIR.

419
00:27:40,960 --> 00:27:43,727
<i> I KNOW.</i>

420
00:27:43,796 --> 00:27:46,063
AT LEAST HE HAS HIS MOTHER
TO TAKE CARE OF HIM.

421
00:27:46,132 --> 00:27:49,599
MY LITTLE MAN.
I DON'T DESERVE HIM.
I REALLY DON'T.

422
00:27:51,637 --> 00:27:54,071
SAW THE MURDER--
HIS CLASS WAS GOING
ON A FIELD TRIP,

423
00:27:54,140 --> 00:27:57,374
AND ERIC WOKE UP
WITH SOME SNIFFLES
AND A FEVER COMING ON,

424
00:27:57,442 --> 00:27:59,509
AND I REALLY SHOULD HAVE
KEPT HIM HOME,

425
00:27:59,578 --> 00:28:01,511
BUT I DIDN'T.

426
00:28:01,580 --> 00:28:05,281
SEE, I HAD MADE PLANS
THAT DAY.
WHAT HAPPENED WASN'T YOUR FAULT.

427
00:28:06,752 --> 00:28:08,685
I AM HIS MOTHER.

428
00:28:08,754 --> 00:28:12,055
I'M SUPPOSED TO KEEP HIM
SAFE AND HAPPY,
AND HE'S NEITHER.

429
00:28:12,124 --> 00:28:14,057
AND THE WORST PART IS...

430
00:28:14,126 --> 00:28:18,362
<i>THAT ONCE THE NEW TRIAL STARTS,</i>
<i>IT'S GONNA START</i>
<i>ALL OVER AGAIN.</i>

431
00:28:23,035 --> 00:28:25,368
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>
<i>QUIETLY, ANGELO.</i>

432
00:28:25,437 --> 00:28:28,672
I'M TAKING YOU TO SEE
A FRIEND OF MINE--
EDNA.

433
00:28:28,740 --> 00:28:32,442
SYDNEY'S FRIEND DEAD.
NO, SHE'S VERY MUCH ALIVE.

434
00:28:32,511 --> 00:28:34,711
NO. DEAD INSIDE.

435
00:28:41,253 --> 00:28:44,187
THAT IS WHY I NEED
YOUR HELP, ANGELO.

436
00:28:44,256 --> 00:28:46,189
GOT IT?

437
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:58,268
- WORKING LATE, SYDNEY?
- ISN'T IT PAST BONZO'S BEDTIME?

438
00:28:58,337 --> 00:29:01,505
I HAVE THIS IDEA...

439
00:29:01,574 --> 00:29:03,806
<i> THAT ANGELO MIGHT</i>
<i> BE ABLE TO EMPATH...</i>

440
00:29:03,875 --> 00:29:07,577
- JAROD'S NEXT MOVE.
- YOUR IDEA WILL HAVE TO WAIT.

441
00:29:07,646 --> 00:29:11,482
<i>ANGELO'S SKILLS ARE REQUIRED</i>
<i>IN ANOTHER PURSUIT</i>
<i>AT THE MOMENT.</i>

442
00:29:12,717 --> 00:29:14,618
THAT A PROBLEM?

443
00:29:15,721 --> 00:29:17,654
NO, OF COURSE NOT.

444
00:29:17,723 --> 00:29:19,523
COME ON, MONKEY BOY.

445
00:29:24,329 --> 00:29:27,363
<i> [ Eric ]</i>
<i> MOM, WHAT'S</i>
<i> GONNA HAPPEN TO US?</i>

446
00:29:27,432 --> 00:29:31,501
<i>I DON'T KNOW, KIDDO.</i>
<i>WE MAY HAVE TO PLAY IT</i>
<i>FAST AND LOOSE AGAIN.</i>

447
00:29:31,570 --> 00:29:34,704
MOM, I CAN'T LEAVE.
NOT YET.

448
00:29:34,773 --> 00:29:37,541
HONEY, I DON'T KNOW
THAT WE HAVE A CHOICE.

449
00:29:37,610 --> 00:29:40,477
- MOM, PLEASE. THERE'S
SOMETHING I HAVE TO DO.
- BABY, I'M SO SORRY.

450
00:29:40,546 --> 00:29:43,680
THIS NEVER SHOULD HAVE
HAPPENED TO YOU.

451
00:29:43,749 --> 00:29:47,317
<i>NOW TRY AND GET</i>
<i>SOME SLEEP. OKAY?</i>

452
00:29:54,160 --> 00:29:56,093
SO WHAT NOW?

453
00:29:58,164 --> 00:30:02,466
THE MARSHAL SAID
THAT ESPOSITO'S MAN
IS SOMEONE INSIDE THE SCHOOL.

454
00:30:02,534 --> 00:30:04,634
I FIND HIM
BEFORE HE FINDS US.

455
00:30:12,277 --> 00:30:14,477
[ Beeping ]

456
00:30:25,290 --> 00:30:27,925
MRS. RAINES,
THAT MONSTER...

457
00:30:27,993 --> 00:30:31,694
YOU'RE MARRIED TO
HAS KEPT YOU DOPED UP
FOR THE LAST 20 YEARS.

458
00:30:31,763 --> 00:30:34,665
WHY? WHAT DID YOU KNOW?

459
00:30:34,733 --> 00:30:36,900
SO GOOD TO SEE YOU AGAIN,
CATHERINE.

460
00:30:38,971 --> 00:30:42,072
THAT'S RIGHT.
I'M CATHERINE, YOUR FRIEND.

461
00:30:42,141 --> 00:30:45,108
I'M HERE TO HELP YOU,
BUT YOU NEED TO HELP ME TOO.

462
00:30:45,177 --> 00:30:47,611
SO GOOD TO SEE YOU AGAIN,
CATHERINE.

463
00:30:47,680 --> 00:30:50,914
AND I KNOW YOU CAME HERE
TO SEE ME FOR A REASON.

464
00:30:50,982 --> 00:30:55,452
PLEASE... TELL ME
WHAT IT IS.

465
00:30:55,521 --> 00:30:57,554
SO GOOD TO SEE YOU AGAIN,
CATHERINE.

466
00:30:57,623 --> 00:31:00,357
LOOK. I'M NOT CATHERINE.

467
00:31:00,425 --> 00:31:02,359
ALL RIGHT?

468
00:31:02,427 --> 00:31:04,794
CATHERINE'S BEEN DEAD
A VERY LONG TIME.

469
00:31:04,863 --> 00:31:07,030
DO YOU HEAR ME?

470
00:31:09,335 --> 00:31:12,970
[ Groans ]
I'M NOT MY MOTHER.

471
00:31:13,038 --> 00:31:15,038
HOW ARE YOUR MUMPS,
LITTLE MISS PARKER?

472
00:31:20,679 --> 00:31:22,613
YOU REMEMBER.

473
00:31:22,682 --> 00:31:25,249
EDNA, PLEASE--

474
00:31:25,317 --> 00:31:28,085
TELL ME WHY
YOU CAME HERE TO SEE ME.

475
00:31:31,057 --> 00:31:34,992
MIRAGE.
"MIRAGE."
WHAT IS MIRAGE?

476
00:31:35,061 --> 00:31:38,128
WHAT YOUR MOTHER STARTED.
WORK SHE HOPED YOU'D FINISH.

477
00:31:38,196 --> 00:31:41,165
WHAT KIND OF WORK?

478
00:31:41,233 --> 00:31:43,933
EDNA? EDNA?

479
00:31:45,137 --> 00:31:47,771
EDNA, STAY WITH ME.

480
00:32:00,886 --> 00:32:03,353
<i> RACHEL.</i>

481
00:32:03,422 --> 00:32:05,489
<i> "RACHEL DALY.</i>
<i> CHICAGO FIELD OFFICE.</i>

482
00:32:05,557 --> 00:32:07,924
"FEDERAL MARSHAL,
WITNESS PROTECTION DIVISION.

483
00:32:07,993 --> 00:32:11,428
<i> CURRENT ASSIGNMENT:</i>
<i> ON LEAVE."</i>
[ Beeping ]

484
00:32:12,564 --> 00:32:14,497
<i>RACHEL DALY.</i>

485
00:32:14,566 --> 00:32:16,567
RACHEL DALY,
THE SCHOOL COUNSELOR?

486
00:32:16,635 --> 00:32:18,969
SHE'S A WITNESS PROTECTION
AGENT FROM OUT OF STATE.

487
00:32:19,037 --> 00:32:20,971
BUT WHY WOULD SHE DO THAT?
MONEY. ERIC'S TESTIMONY...

488
00:32:21,040 --> 00:32:23,040
IS THE ONLY THING
THAT COULD PUT ESPOSITO
BACK IN PRISON.

489
00:32:23,108 --> 00:32:25,041
WHERE IS HE?
UH, HE'S STILL SLEEPING.

490
00:32:25,110 --> 00:32:27,044
I DIDN'T WANT TO WAKE HIM
TILL I HAD TO.

491
00:32:27,113 --> 00:32:29,212
WE HAVE TO GET
YOU TWO OUT OF TOWN.
I'LL DEAL WITH RACHEL LATER.

492
00:32:31,450 --> 00:32:33,850
OH, MY GOD, THEY GOT HIM.
ERIC!

493
00:32:33,919 --> 00:32:37,988
<i>ERIC!</i>
NO. THIS WASN'T FORCED OPEN.
IT WAS UNLOCKED FROM THE INSIDE.

494
00:32:38,057 --> 00:32:40,190
BUT WHY? WHERE WOULD HE GO?

495
00:32:40,259 --> 00:32:42,992
-<i> [ School Bell Ringing ]</i>
- [ Chattering ]

496
00:32:43,061 --> 00:32:45,062
<i>♪♪ [ Pop On P.A. ]</i>

497
00:32:48,867 --> 00:32:51,701
HEY. HI.
UH, MOLLY,

498
00:32:51,770 --> 00:32:54,037
CAN I TALK TO YOU
FOR A SEC?

499
00:32:57,743 --> 00:33:00,510
THERE'S SOMEWHERE
I HAVE TO GO.

500
00:33:00,579 --> 00:33:02,545
YOU KNOW,
IT'S A SECRET MISSION,

501
00:33:02,615 --> 00:33:05,715
BUT I DIDN'T WANT TO LEAVE
BEFORE I TOLD YOU SOMETHING.

502
00:33:05,784 --> 00:33:07,718
YEAH? WHAT?

503
00:33:07,787 --> 00:33:10,019
ALL YEAR LONG, I--

504
00:33:11,156 --> 00:33:14,091
NO. NO, I'M SORRY.
THAT'S NOT WHAT I MEANT.

505
00:33:18,063 --> 00:33:19,996
HERE.

506
00:33:20,065 --> 00:33:22,265
UH, CAN YOU JUST
LISTEN TO THIS?

507
00:33:22,334 --> 00:33:24,735
- PLEASE?
- SURE.

508
00:33:26,138 --> 00:33:28,338
SORRY TO INTERRUPT
YOUR LOVE CONNECTION,

509
00:33:28,407 --> 00:33:30,907
BUT YOU ALREADY GOT A DATE--
WITH MY FIST.

510
00:33:51,796 --> 00:33:53,730
ERIC.

511
00:33:53,798 --> 00:33:55,732
JUST THE YOUNG MAN
I WAS LOOKING FOR.
WHY DON'T YOU COME WITH ME?

512
00:33:55,801 --> 00:33:58,268
THERE'S SOMEONE HERE
TO SEE YOU.

513
00:34:00,372 --> 00:34:02,305
HEY THERE, BUDDY.
REMEMBER ME?

514
00:34:11,650 --> 00:34:13,249
ERIC! ERIC!

515
00:34:13,318 --> 00:34:14,985
<i> [ Jarod ]</i>
<i> MOLLY.</i>

516
00:34:15,054 --> 00:34:18,555
- HAVE YOU SEEN ERIC GANTRY?
- THAT JERK JOEL
CHASED HIM THAT WAY.

517
00:34:24,262 --> 00:34:26,830
ERIC! ERIC!

518
00:34:29,735 --> 00:34:31,735
OH, MY GOD. SHE HAS HIM.

519
00:34:31,804 --> 00:34:33,771
JAROD, WHAT ARE WE
GONNA DO?

520
00:34:33,839 --> 00:34:36,540
WHERE COULD THEY
HAVE TAKEN HIM?
WAIT A MINUTE.

521
00:34:38,611 --> 00:34:41,044
SMART BOY, ERIC.
[ Tape Rewinding ]

522
00:34:41,112 --> 00:34:43,112
[ Eric On Tape ]
LEAVE ME ALONE.
[ Esposito ] SHUT UP.

523
00:34:43,181 --> 00:34:44,914
MY GOD.

524
00:34:44,983 --> 00:34:47,751
<i> WHERE ARE YOU TAKING ME?</i>
<i>DON'T WORRY, KID.</i>
<i>IT'S A SHORT WALK.</i>

525
00:34:47,820 --> 00:34:51,254
<i>SORRY I DIDN'T BRING</i>
<i>A HARD HAT.</i>
<i> [ Daly ] COME ON, ERIC.</i>

526
00:34:51,323 --> 00:34:53,256
<i> LET ME GO!</i>
CALL THE POLICE.

527
00:34:54,626 --> 00:34:56,560
<i> [ Eric ]</i>
<i> COME ON!</i>

528
00:34:56,629 --> 00:34:59,563
<i> I SWEAR TO GOD,</i>
<i> I WILL NOT TESTIFY</i>
<i> AGAINST YOU.</i>

529
00:34:59,632 --> 00:35:01,565
PLEASE LET ME GO!
SORRY, KID, BUT AS LONG
AS YOU'RE ALIVE,

530
00:35:01,634 --> 00:35:04,401
YOU STAND TO SERIOUSLY
FOUL UP MY LIFE.

531
00:35:04,470 --> 00:35:07,637
GET IN THE HOLE.
NO!

532
00:35:07,706 --> 00:35:09,639
BE A GOOD BOY, ERIC,
AND DO AS HE SAYS.

533
00:35:11,143 --> 00:35:13,309
BOTH OF YOU.

534
00:35:13,378 --> 00:35:16,379
<i> WHY DON'T YOU</i>
<i> FILL IT YOURSELF?</i>

535
00:35:24,355 --> 00:35:26,289
THANK GOD, JAROD.

536
00:35:26,358 --> 00:35:29,726
- I SAW HIM DRAGGING ERIC HERE
AND I DIDN'T--
- I KNOW, I KNOW.

537
00:35:29,795 --> 00:35:32,929
<i>YOU KNOW SOMETHING?</i>
<i>I DON'T THINK THIS HOLE</i>
<i>IS FULL ENOUGH.</i>

538
00:35:32,998 --> 00:35:35,932
OH!

539
00:35:37,002 --> 00:35:39,302
YOU OKAY?
UH, YEAH.

540
00:35:39,371 --> 00:35:42,272
GOOD. YOU GO TAKE CARE
OF YOUR MOM NOW. GO.
OKAY.

541
00:35:46,979 --> 00:35:48,912
IT'S KIND OF FITTING,
DON'T YOU THINK?

542
00:35:48,981 --> 00:35:50,980
<i> YOU'VE GOTTEN YOURSELVES</i>
<i> INTO A HOLE...</i>

543
00:35:51,049 --> 00:35:53,650
YOU CAN'T GET OUT OF.

544
00:35:53,718 --> 00:35:56,352
JAROD, COME ON.
COME ON. WE WERE JUST
TALKING TO THAT KID.

545
00:35:56,421 --> 00:35:59,156
OH, YES, LIKE THE WAY
SHE WAS JUST TALKING...

546
00:35:59,224 --> 00:36:01,591
<i> TO THAT FEDERAL MARSHAL--</i>
<i> WHEN SHE MURDERED HIM,</i>

547
00:36:01,660 --> 00:36:04,027
OR THE WAY YOU WERE JUST
TALKING TO THE SHOP OWNER...

548
00:36:04,096 --> 00:36:06,697
<i> TWO YEARS AGO</i>
<i> WHEN HE WAS BLUDGEONED</i>
<i> TO DEATH.</i>

549
00:36:10,268 --> 00:36:12,369
<i> OH. WHOA, WHOA.</i>
<i> WHAT ARE YOU DOING?</i>

550
00:36:14,339 --> 00:36:16,273
JAROD?

551
00:36:19,278 --> 00:36:21,944
JAROD, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
HE'S CRAZY.

552
00:36:22,013 --> 00:36:24,147
<i> ERIC WAS JUST A BOY.</i>

553
00:36:24,216 --> 00:36:26,683
<i> ALL HE WANTED</i>
<i> WAS HIS CHILDHOOD--</i>

554
00:36:26,752 --> 00:36:28,785
TO BE WITH HIS FAMILY,
TO PLAY WITH HIS FRIENDS.

555
00:36:28,854 --> 00:36:31,354
<i> BUT YOU TOOK</i>
<i> ALL THAT AWAY FROM HIM.</i>

556
00:36:31,423 --> 00:36:34,056
IN AN INSTANT,
EVERYTHING HE KNEW
WAS JUST TAKEN AWAY.

557
00:36:35,694 --> 00:36:37,460
WELL, NOW IT'S YOUR TURN
TO DISAPPEAR,

558
00:36:37,529 --> 00:36:40,697
<i> AND NO ONE</i>
<i> WILL EVER MISS YOU.</i>

559
00:36:40,765 --> 00:36:43,533
<i>OKAY, I DID SELL ERIC OUT,</i>

560
00:36:43,602 --> 00:36:47,504
AND I DID SHOOT THE MARSHAL,
BUT I CAN HELP YOU OUT.

561
00:36:47,573 --> 00:36:49,873
I CAN TESTIFY
AGAINST ESPOSITO.
SHUT UP!

562
00:36:49,942 --> 00:36:52,342
I DON'T KNOW.
WHY DON'T YOU OFFER HER
SOME MORE MONEY, ESPOSITO?

563
00:36:52,411 --> 00:36:55,745
- YOU'RE INSANE.
YOU CAN'T DO THIS.
- WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?

564
00:36:55,814 --> 00:36:57,747
I'M JUST A GUY
WHO'S DIGGING YOUR GRAVE.

565
00:36:57,816 --> 00:37:01,017
OH, THAT'S RIGHT--
YOU TWO ALREADY DUG IT.
I'M JUST FILLING IT IN.

566
00:37:03,788 --> 00:37:06,723
<i> YOU BETTER TALK QUICK.</i>
<i> THIS STUFF DRIES FAST.</i>

567
00:37:06,792 --> 00:37:09,759
ALL RIGHT!
ALL RIGHT, I DID IT!
I SAID I DID IT.

568
00:37:12,898 --> 00:37:16,399
- COME AGAIN?
- I KILLED THE SHOP OWNER.

569
00:37:16,468 --> 00:37:19,069
I HIRED HER TO KILL THE KID.
IS THAT WHAT YOU WANT TO HEAR?

570
00:37:19,137 --> 00:37:22,239
YES. AS A MATTER
OF FACT, IT IS.
[ Tape Rewinding ]

571
00:37:22,307 --> 00:37:25,408
[ Esposito On Tape ]
I KILLED THE SHOP OWNER
AND I HIRED HER TO KILL THE KID.

572
00:37:25,477 --> 00:37:27,410
IS THAT WHAT
YOU WANT TO HEAR?

573
00:37:27,479 --> 00:37:30,347
YOU'RE STILL
GOING TO DISAPPEAR--
BOTH OF YOU.

574
00:37:32,751 --> 00:37:35,218
<i>[ Daly ] WHAT ARE YOU DOING?</i>
<i>[ Esposito ]</i>
<i>I GAVE YOU WHAT YOU WANTED.</i>

575
00:37:35,287 --> 00:37:37,787
<i>[ Daly, Esposito Shouting ]</i>

576
00:37:40,359 --> 00:37:43,794
<i>JAROD! YOU CAN'T JUST</i>
<i>LEAVE US IN HERE.</i>
<i>WAIT! WAIT!</i>

577
00:37:43,862 --> 00:37:46,129
<i>JAROD!</i>

578
00:37:46,198 --> 00:37:48,131
<i> WHAT ABOUT MIRAGE?</i>
<i> ANYTHING YET?</i>

579
00:37:48,200 --> 00:37:50,133
UH--
[ Clears Throat ]

580
00:37:50,202 --> 00:37:54,037
WELL, I'VE, UH--
I'VE SCANNED THE D.S.A.
FILE DIRECTORY, AND--

581
00:37:54,106 --> 00:37:56,405
THE HEADLINES, BROOTS.
NOT THE FINE PRINT.

582
00:37:56,474 --> 00:37:58,641
NO. NOTHING ON MIRAGE.

583
00:37:58,710 --> 00:38:02,411
MAYBE IT'S JUST NONSENSE.
I MEAN, THIS LADY IS
A LITTLE WHACKED-OUT.

584
00:38:02,480 --> 00:38:04,981
MOST OF THE TIME, YEAH,
BUT NOT WHEN SHE
SAID MIRAGE.

585
00:38:05,050 --> 00:38:06,983
I KNOW IT.

586
00:38:07,052 --> 00:38:09,385
SO--
IT'S BACK
TO THE SALT MINES FOR ME.

587
00:39:08,613 --> 00:39:10,714
<i>[ Bell Ringing ]</i>

588
00:39:12,117 --> 00:39:14,350
COME ON, JOEL.

589
00:39:14,419 --> 00:39:16,552
WHAT DID YOU BRING
FOR ME TODAY, FREAK?

590
00:39:16,621 --> 00:39:19,989
WHAT'S THIS? BROWNIES?

591
00:39:20,058 --> 00:39:21,991
OH.

592
00:39:22,060 --> 00:39:24,027
DON'T, JOEL.
YOU'LL BE SORRY.

593
00:39:24,096 --> 00:39:26,663
OH, I HAVEN'T
BEEN SORRY YET.

594
00:39:29,068 --> 00:39:31,134
[ Snickers ]

595
00:39:33,272 --> 00:39:35,338
MMM!

596
00:39:35,407 --> 00:39:37,740
MMM! THAT'S GOOD.

597
00:39:39,277 --> 00:39:42,011
TOO BAD YOUR MOTHER
DIDN'T MAKE YOU ANY, FREAK.

598
00:39:49,053 --> 00:39:50,987
PATIENCE.

599
00:39:51,055 --> 00:39:53,389
<i>IT WON'T BE LONG,</i>
<i>WITH THE AMOUNT...</i>

600
00:39:53,458 --> 00:39:55,391
OF PRUNE EXTRACT
WE PUT IN 'EM.

601
00:39:55,460 --> 00:39:59,229
I WOULD SAY RIGHT...
ABOUT...

602
00:39:59,298 --> 00:40:01,497
NOW.

603
00:40:01,566 --> 00:40:03,733
[ Rumbling ]

604
00:40:13,178 --> 00:40:15,312
I WONDER WHAT
CAME OVER HIM.

605
00:40:15,380 --> 00:40:17,847
SOMETHING HE ATE, MAYBE?

606
00:40:17,916 --> 00:40:19,916
HMM.

607
00:40:27,659 --> 00:40:32,395
<i> [ Laughing, Chattering ]</i>

608
00:40:34,866 --> 00:40:37,200
NO!

609
00:40:41,973 --> 00:40:45,074
WELL, AGENT GANTRY,
MISSION ACCOMPLISHED.

610
00:40:45,143 --> 00:40:47,744
MISSION ACCOMPLISHED.

611
00:40:49,381 --> 00:40:51,948
<i>[ Bell Ringing ]</i>

612
00:40:58,156 --> 00:41:00,824
EXCUSE ME.
SEEN THE PAPER
THIS MORNING?

613
00:41:00,892 --> 00:41:02,892
NOW, I CAN'T UNDERSTAND...

614
00:41:02,961 --> 00:41:06,162
<i>HOW THEY GOT THE STORY,</i>
<i>AND YET THERE'S NOT</i>
<i>ONE MENTION ABOUT THE GUY...</i>

615
00:41:06,231 --> 00:41:09,999
WHO MADE IT ALL HAPPEN.
TEACHING CAN BE SUCH
A THANKLESS PROFESSION.

616
00:41:10,068 --> 00:41:12,001
NOT ENTIRELY.

617
00:41:14,472 --> 00:41:18,741
- THANK YOU, JAROD.
- THANKS, MR. BRODIE.

618
00:41:21,846 --> 00:41:24,247
<i> ERIC, CAN I TALK</i>
<i> TO YOU FOR A SEC?</i>

619
00:41:30,121 --> 00:41:32,222
I LISTENED TO YOUR TAPE.

620
00:41:32,290 --> 00:41:34,624
IT WAS SWEET.
I'M REALLY GLAD
YOU GAVE IT TO ME.

621
00:41:34,693 --> 00:41:37,694
- REALLY?
- MM-HMM.

622
00:41:37,762 --> 00:41:39,895
SO I WAS WONDERING--

623
00:41:39,964 --> 00:41:42,799
DO YOU WANT TO GO
TO THE SADIE HAWKINS DANCE
WITH ME TOMORROW NIGHT?

624
00:41:42,867 --> 00:41:44,867
YEAH! I-I MEAN--

625
00:41:44,936 --> 00:41:47,937
- OF COURSE I DO.
- GOOD.

626
00:41:48,006 --> 00:41:50,807
I'LL... SEE YOU IN CLASS.

627
00:41:58,449 --> 00:42:00,383
MOM, WE DON'T HAVE
TO LEAVE TONIGHT, DO WE?

628
00:42:00,452 --> 00:42:03,886
DOES A CERTAIN SECRET AGENT
HAVE ONE LAST RENDEZVOUS?

629
00:42:05,256 --> 00:42:08,290
YEAH.

630
00:42:10,528 --> 00:42:12,462
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>SHE OKAY, SAM?</i>

631
00:42:12,530 --> 00:42:15,398
SHE WENT AND LAID DOWN.
I HAVEN'T HEARD
A WORD FROM HER.

632
00:42:17,102 --> 00:42:19,402
MRS. RAINES? EDNA?

633
00:42:23,742 --> 00:42:25,675
[ Whispering ]
OH, MAN.

634
00:42:28,212 --> 00:42:30,146
NOW WE'RE LEFT
EMPTY-HANDED.

635
00:42:32,784 --> 00:42:34,717
NOT EXACTLY.

636
00:42:36,321 --> 00:42:38,254
I STILL HAVE MIRAGE.

637
00:43:01,479 --> 00:43:03,679
♪ KRI KRA TOAD'S FOOT ♪

638
00:43:03,748 --> 00:43:06,182
♪ GEESE WALK BAREFOOT ♪

639
00:43:06,251 --> 00:43:08,184
<i>[ Vehicle Approaching ]</i>

640
00:43:08,253 --> 00:43:10,286
♪ KRI KRA TOAD'S FOOT-- ♪

641
00:43:29,374 --> 00:43:31,875
<i>[ Edna ]</i>
<i>♪ KRI KRA TOAD'S FOOT ♪</i>

642
00:43:31,943 --> 00:43:34,210
<i>♪ GEESE WALK BAREFOOT ♪♪</i>

